article.headline: Terrence Edwards scores 20, James Madison wins 67-52 over Marshall

images.name: T.J. Bickerstaff tosses assist from the ground
images.caption: T.J. Bickerstaff finds Julien Wooden while seated on the court for a James Madison jam.

article.linkText: Terrence Edwards scores 20, James Madison wins 67-52 over Marshall
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. -- — Terrence Edwards' 20 points helped James Madison defeat Marshall 67-52 on Saturday night. Edwards also added five assists for the Dukes (17-2, 6-2 Sun Belt Conference). Noah Freidel added 14 points while going 4 of 9 from the floor, including 3 for 7 from 3-point range, and 3 for 4 from the line, and he also had eight rebounds. Jaylen Carey had 10 points and finished 5 of 6 from the field. Kamdyn Curfman led the Thundering Herd (9-11, 4-3) in scoring, finishing with 23 points. Kevon Voyles added 11 points and six rebounds for Marshall. In addition, Wyatt Fricks had seven points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
